resources.string: Child-Headed or Female Headed or Elderly Headed or Disabled Headed Household
1. Child-headed households (orphan-headed households or where the parent or grandparent is incapable of undertaking the usual head of household roles)
2. Elderly-headed households (more than 60 years old) with no other able-bodied adult household members.
3. The most food insecure households with chronically ill/HIV or AIDS affected members
5. Households with two or more years of successive crop failure
6. Households with children receiving supplementary or therapeutic feeding
